The body of the late former education CS George Magoha has arrived at in Siaya ahead of his burial on Saturday. The body was airlifted from Nairobi aboard a Kenya Airforce helicopter. The chopper landed at the Yala Township Primary shortly after 2pm Friday. A somber mood engulfed residents of Yala who were on call to receive the body of the late professor in his hometown. According to the family, Magoha will be laid to rest at 11 am on Saturday at his home in Yala, Siaya county. The burial will be preceded by a funeral mass at Odera Akang’o University College. On Thursday, a requiem mass for Magoha was held at the Consolate Shrine in Westlands from at 9am. Family, friends and colleagues paid glowing tributes to the late professor of surgery.